Let‚Äôa make Green Tea Eggs with @higher_living_australia 

I‚Äôve used the Green Tea Chai teabags to make a really flavourful base for my tea eggs. This recipe is so easy and it‚Äôs a great way to dress up the humble boiled egg. 

All you need to do is make the flavour base by boiling (for 4 eggs)
‚Ä¢ 1-2 cups of water
‚Ä¢ 2 tbsp soy sauce
‚Ä¢ 1-2 tea bags
‚Ä¢ 2 bay leaves
‚Ä¢ 1/2 inch stick of cinnamon
‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Sichuan peppercorns
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp of sugar
‚Ä¢ pinch of salt

Then boil room temperature eggs for 7 minutes, and then remove and cool in an ice bath.

Crack the shells of the eggs (or remove completely) and place into a container. Pour over the prepared soy mixture (cooled) and set in the fridge for at least 12 hours. 

Serve with noodles or eat them plain - because they are delicious!
